# New Chat Session Bootstrap

At the start of every new chat session, orient yourself before making any plans or edits.
Run these commands immediately -- do not skip them even for seemingly simple requests.

## Step 1 -- Understand recent changes (run first, always)

```bash
git log --oneline -10              # what changed across recent sessions
git log --name-only --oneline -5   # which specific files changed in the last 5 commits
git status --short                 # any uncommitted edits right now
```

Read the commit messages and file list carefully. They tell you what a previous agent
already did so you do not repeat work or undo changes.

## Step 2 -- Check process health

```bash
pm2 list                           # verify litreview-api (port 8001) and litreview-ui are online
pm2 logs litreview-api --lines 20  # catch any recent backend crashes
```

If `litreview-api` is stopped or erroring, fix that before starting new work.

## Step 3 -- Check the project overview rule

`project-overview-always.mdc` (always in context) is the authoritative map of every
backend module (`src/`) and frontend component (`frontend/src/`). Re-read the relevant
section before touching an unfamiliar module.

The key directories added in recent sessions that are NOT yet widely referenced:
- `src/rag/` -- RAG pipeline (chunker, embedder, retriever)
- `src/knowledge_graph/` -- evidence network (builder, community, gap_detector)
- `src/orchestration/embedding_node.py`, `src/orchestration/knowledge_graph_node.py`

## Step 4 -- Production deploy reminder

The production URL (`https://litreview.parthchandak.info`) is served by FastAPI on port 8000
via Cloudflare tunnel. It serves the **built** `frontend/dist/` -- NOT the Vite dev server.

After any frontend code change, the production site stays stale until you rebuild:

```bash
cd frontend && pnpm build && cd ..
pm2 restart litreview-api
```

The Vite dev server (localhost:5173) picks up changes automatically; the production URL does not.

## Known gotchas (distilled from past sessions)

- **PRISMA checklist**: the API reads `doc_manuscript.md` from the run dir, not `manuscript.md`.
  Fixed in commit `3180f25`. If the PRISMA card shows "data not available", check the file exists.
- **Run directory layout**: `runs/YYYY-MM-DD/<slug>/run_<HH-MM-SSam>/runtime.db`
  (4 levels under `runs/`). Path math that assumes fewer levels will silently read the wrong dir.
- **Frontend visible on localhost but not production**: always suspect a stale `frontend/dist/`.
  Run `pnpm build` and restart `litreview-api`.
- **Backend changes not taking effect**: Python loads modules at startup. Restart `litreview-api`
  after any `src/` edit, or the running process uses the pre-edit code.
- **Historical run PRISMA/results endpoints**: require the run to be registered in `_active_runs`.
  Use `POST /api/history/attach` to re-register a completed run before calling PRISMA/results APIs.
